Question 2
We are interested in creating a marketing campaign to target customers based on their spending score and annual income. Perform a k-means clustering to find if there are meaningful clusters in the data to target the customers.

<!-- rnb-text-end -->


<!-- rnb-chunk-begin -->


<!-- rnb-source-begin eyJkYXRhIjoiYGBgclxuc2NhbGVkIDwtIGN1c3RvbWVycyAlPiUgXG4gIHNlbGVjdChhbm51YWxfaW5jb21lX2ssXG4gICAgICAgICBzcGVuZGluZ19zY29yZV8xXzEwMCkgJT4lIFxuICBtdXRhdGVfYWxsKHNjYWxlKVxuYGBgIn0= -->

```r
scaled <- customers %>% 
  select(annual_income_k,
         spending_score_1_100) %>% 
  mutate_all(scale)
```

<!-- rnb-source-end -->

<!-- rnb-chunk-end -->


<!-- rnb-text-begin -->




<!-- rnb-text-end -->


<!-- rnb-chunk-begin -->


<!-- rnb-source-begin eyJkYXRhIjoiYGBgclxuZnZpel9uYmNsdXN0KHNjYWxlZCxcbiAgICAgICAgICAgICBrbWVhbnMsXG4gICAgICAgICAgICAgbWV0aG9kID0gXCJ3c3NcIixcbiAgICAgICAgICAgICBuc3RhcnQgPSA1MClcbmBgYCJ9 -->

```r
fviz_nbclust(scaled,
             kmeans,
             method = "wss",
             nstart = 50)
```

<!-- rnb-source-end -->

<!-- rnb-output-begin eyJkYXRhIjoiUmVnaXN0ZXJlZCBTMyBtZXRob2Qgb3ZlcndyaXR0ZW4gYnkgJ2RhdGEudGFibGUnOlxuICBtZXRob2QgICAgICAgICAgIGZyb21cbiAgcHJpbnQuZGF0YS50YWJsZSAgICAgXG4ifQ== -->
